caller_intent: Cassandra Mitchell contacted Alliance Insurance to resolve confusion about a notice from her landlord stating her renter's insurance had expired, and to clarify the policy status and payment details.
resolution_steps: Agent confirmed Cassandra's renter's policy was still active.
Agent explained the $127.50 payment was due on August 10th and auto-pay was set up.
Cassandra requested to forward the landlord's notice to Alliance's support email for documentation.
Agent provided the support email address (support@allianceinsurance.com) and confirmed the email would be sent to the team.
Agent sent the email and confirmed receipt with Cassandra.
knowledge_required: Support email procedures for documentation sharing
summary: Cassandra Mitchell contacted Alliance Insurance to address a landlord notice claiming her renter's insurance had expired. The agent clarified the policy was active, explained the upcoming auto-pay, and facilitated forwarding the notice to the support team via email. The call concluded with confirmation that the email was sent and the issue resolved.
